  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Choirs To Improve English Literacy of 600 Children</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The ISIPHETHU SOTHUKELA Project has demonstrated that initiating a choir in schools of impoverished areas can effect a  40% improvement in English Literacy. This project focuses on leadership development of principals and empowerment of teachers through mentorship, to upgrade Maths, Science and English teaching of learners already well-disciplined through choir participation. The Siyacula (&quot;We Sing&quot;) Music Festival  celebrates   progress annually in a joint concert with project partners</narrative>
  </description>
